<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- M1 (Eb→③→④): Opening ① 4-note Eb2-Bb2-Eb3-G3; ③ Gm + ④ Ab passing tones in RH
- M2-3: ①/⑥/④ progression — RH stays high (Eb5); LH tracks roots smoothly
- M3: ⑦° D° = D2-Ab2-D3-F3 — rich dim texture
- M4: ⑤² second inversion hold — F4 Bb4 D5 creates suspension
- M7: ⑥7 Cm7 = C2-G2-Bb2-Eb3 full bass — emotional depth
- M8/M12: ⑤ Bb "333" Bb4-D5-F5 RH — mid-cadences
- M10: ① ascending arpeggiation in melody — harp sustains 4-note Eb throughout
- M11: four chords in one measure — fastest harmonic rhythm in piece
- M14: ① held dotted half then ② Fm pickup into final cadence
- M15: ① "334" G5 highest note; ⑤ Bb D5-F5-Bb4 — final approach
- M16: ① "334" G4-Bb4-Eb5-G5 full close, Eb1 pedal

VOICE LEADING:
- M1→2: Bb4 common RH across ①→①
- M5→6: Bb4 sustained pedal ⑤→⑥ both have Bb
- M11: four-chord bar — all voices move, bass walks Cm→Gm→Ab→Eb (stepwise)
- M15→16: G5 in RH is highest pitch; descends to Eb5 for final close

TEXTURE ARC:
- M1-4: Light cut-time feel — half-note blocks, subtle passing notes in RH
- M5-8: Growing — fuller Eb "333" voicing in RH, Cm7 bass depth
- M9-12: Middle section — ascending figure M10 creates lightness; M11 most active
- M13-14: Penultimate phrase — ①"33" with high Eb5; ② anticipation
- M15-16: Climax and resolution — ①"334" G5, full close with Eb1 pedal
-->
